Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Halve, peel and
thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Add the onion to the pan with a pinch of
@salt{} and sugar (if you have some). Lower the heat to medium and cook until
softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest the @lemon{1/2} and mix with half the @easy garlic{1}(minced),
a squeeze of lemon juice and the @oil for the pork{1%tbsp} in a #mixing bowl{}.
Season with a pinch of salt and @ground black pepper{}. Add the
@British pork loin steaks{2} and coat in the marinade.

Lay the pork steaks on your #baking tray{} and grill for ~{5-6%minutes} on each
side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

When cooked, remove the pork from under the grill and wrap loosely in #foil{}.

> IMPORTANT: The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the onions are soft, add the @dried oregano{1%tsp} and remaining garlic.
Cook for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @wholegrain mustard{1} and
@apple chutney{1}, cook for another ~{1%minute}. Drain, rinse and add the
@lentils{1%cup} to the pan with the @water for the lentils{50%ml}. Lower the
heat to medium and cook until the water has evaporated, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir
occasionally. Stir the @baby spinach{125%g} into the lentils one handful at a
time until just wilted.

Halve the @ciabatta{1} (as if you were making a sandwich). Drizzle with a little
oil and season with salt and pepper. A few minutes before you are ready to
serve, pop the ciabatta under the grill on another baking tray until golden and
toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Meanwhile, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped).

Stir half the parsley through the lentils. Season to taste with salt and
pepper. Slice the pork into thin strips. Serve the lentils topped with the
pork and finished with a sprinkling of the remaining parsley. Chop each
ciabatta slice in half and serve alongside the pork.